summary:
Another thing I like about Villanelle is how weird she is. 
Like, they totally could have made her a sterotypical suave and...
body:
Another thing I like about Villanelle is how weird she is.

Like, they totally could have made her a sterotypical suave and seductive killer type but instead she’s a weirdo that does things like wear a fake beard just to annoy Konstatin and straight up tells the woman she’s infatuated with that she “masturbates to her a lot”.

She wasn’t made to appeal to the male gaze at all and I love it.

summary: Not only did Danai Gurira and Terry Crews look sharp announcing the Golden Globe Nominations, but all my faves were...
body:
Not only did Danai Gurira and Terry Crews look sharp announcing the Golden Globe Nominations, but all my faves were nominated.

The fact that Regina King is nominated for two different awards for both Seven Seconds and If Beale Street Could Talk is blowing my mind. This is well deserved!

Thandie Newton is nominated for Westworld.

Billy Porter is nominated for Pose.

John David Washington is nominated for Black Klansman as is Adam Driver and the movie itself is nominated. Even Spike received a nomination.

Barry Jenkins was nominated for If Beale Street Could Talk.

Rami Malek was nominated for Bohemian Rhapsody.

Mahershala Ali was nominated for The GreenBook.

Jim Carrey was nominated for Kidding.

Henry Winkler and Bill Hader were nominated for Barry.

Sandra Oh was Nominated for Killing Eve.

Constance Wu was nominated for Crazy Rich Asians.

Pose, Killing Eve, American Crime Story Versace, Homecoming, Barry and Kidding were nominated.
